00:00:30.080 --> 00:00:37.020
MURUKKU FLOUR AT HOME
1. Take a raw rice .keep aside.

00:00:37.200 --> 00:00:49.440
2.In a pan dry roast the urad dal till nice
aroma comes upto 2-5 minutes at medium flame.

00:00:49.449 --> 00:00:55.120
3.When it is cool ,mix both raw rice and roast
urad dal.

00:00:55.120 --> 00:00:59.460
4.Grind in flour mill and it to a fine powder
is called murukku flour.

00:00:59.460 --> 00:01:01.820
PREPARATION

00:01:02.060 --> 00:01:03.680
1.Heat oil in a kadai for deep frying.

00:01:03.720 --> 00:01:13.280
2.In a mixing bowl ,add murukku flour,cumin
seeds,butter,asafoetida,sesame seeds,enough

00:01:13.280 --> 00:01:17.520
salt and mix well .

00:01:17.580 --> 00:01:28.180
3.Add then add water little way and make a
soft dough.

00:01:28.280 --> 00:01:40.560
4.Take a handful of dough and place this in
a murukku maker.

00:01:40.560 --> 00:01:53.820
5.Make&nbsp; round shape 
in a paper towel and transfer into the oil
and cook it in a medium flame until golden

00:01:53.820 --> 00:01:56.300
colour.

00:01:56.300 --> 00:02:13.260
6. Now crispy thenkuzhal murukku is ready
to serve with hot tea.

